    • Constructor Detail

      • Thresholds

        public Thresholds(BuildObjectsFromExcel bofe,
                  java.lang.String name,
                  boolean rule1,
                  boolean rule2,
                  boolean rule3,
                  boolean rule4,
                  boolean logicalOperator1,
                  boolean logicalOperator2,
                  int LOCVal,
                  int CYCLOVal,
                  int AFTDVal,
                  float LAAVal)
        Creates the Threshold with the specific parameters.
        Parameters:
        bofe - Is an object of type BuildObjetsFromExcel that helps reading the excel file
        name - Is the name of the Threshold.
        rule1 - Active(true) or inactive(false) for LOC.
        rule2 - Active or inactive for CYCLO.
        rule3 - Active or inactive for AFTD.
        rule4 - Active or inactive for LAA.
        logicalOperator1 - AND(true) or OR(false) for is_long_method.
        logicalOperator2 - AND or OR for is_feature_envy.
        LOCVal - value of LOC threshold.
        CYCLOVal - value of CYCLO threshold.
        AFTDVal - value of AFTD threshold.
        LAAVal - value of LAA threshold.
